        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> You've been playing for nearly 2 whole years now and your highest guy is around level 20?  If that's the case you don't have a problem with EQ at all.  I have only been playing maybe 2.5 years, have a 60 mage, 51 necro and a few more 40+ toons.  I just quit the other day because I was really starting to have some of the same problems you listed or had already gone through them.  Just ask yourself what you find most rewarding in life.  For me, I chose a meaningful relationship in the end over my "virtual friends".  I did totally loose contact with all my other real life/non EQ related friends when I got into EQ so much, not that I really regret that part.  EQ will die before long, many people are going to be left hanging with no social life/skills.  My advice is get out while you can if your having any troubles such as these.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=236080" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=236080</a></font></td>
