        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Jester, a lot of people don't realize when it can start to become 'more harm than good'.  Everyone has an easy addiction to something or another. Long as you realize what your easy addiction is and either 1) Control it and continue it, or 2) simply cut it off and find something else.<BR>I'm a pretty firm believer in not jumping the gun on saying, "You're an EQ addict! You should stop cause you're gonna die from it!" or some other rediculous non-sensical thing to that effect. However, from your post, it sounds less like you're addicted to EQ and more into the making yourself happy thing. (You like logging on to EQ cause you have friends here, can do fun things in the game, and get a kick out of leveling up/finding new gear/socializing) Hey, that's great and cool.. but I get this nagging feeling after reading your post that you may just be feeling like you need to spend more time with your girlfriend. If that's what you wanna do, go for it. Don't bother with EQ for a while. Maybe ever again. Either way you go, it's not like it's a one time choice. You can log into EQ tommorow, or a year from now. It'll be there. (or EQ2, etc) For now, go hang out with your girlfriend for a solid week or two and see how that goes. Don't try to get others into EQ, and in fact, don't even bring it up and try hard not to think about it. Really let yourself get pulled into something else. Go to a themepark, take her out to the Movies a few times, eat at a new resturaunt, go play Mini-golf with her.. buy some old board games and see how much fun they can be (silly trivia games are great). Discover (or invent) new sex toys! Just do something else for a while and in a few weeks, if you're bored sometime, log onto EQ and goof off. That's what it was for in the first place. <img src=icon_smile.gif border=0 align=middle></P><P></P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=205091" target="_blank